03:51.880 --> 03:54.553
[CHIMP CHATTERS]

04:04.880 --> 04:06.518
You lose.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.752
Again.

04:12.040 --> 04:14.076
I changed your flight sequence.

04:14.480 --> 04:16.072
That's enough.

04:16.560 --> 04:17.754
Pay attention.

04:17.959 --> 04:20.110
Pericles, stop! Or no treat!

04:23.920 --> 04:25.592
How well do I know you?

05:05.040 --> 05:06.951
Hey, there you are.

05:07.920 --> 05:10.309
Was the homo sapien mean to you?

05:10.640 --> 05:12.835
We all know it's just rocket envy.

05:13.040 --> 05:16.669
-Ever consider a boyfriend?
-Do I enjoy being miserable?

05:16.920 --> 05:19.070
-I'll stick with my chimps.
LEO: Hey.

05:24.400 --> 05:26.755
-I'm teaching him.
-You're teasing him.

05:26.960 --> 05:30.794
He's gene-spliced, chromosome-
enhanced. He can handle it.

05:31.000 --> 05:35.630
When you frustrate them, they lose
focus. They even get violent.

05:35.960 --> 05:38.838
Hey, Pericles,
you're gonna be a daddy.

05:39.720 --> 05:44.396
-Thought I saw a smirk on his face.
-The female was the aggressor.

05:44.600 --> 05:46.795
Hey, Leo. You got a postcard.

05:50.720 --> 05:51.709
Leo!

05:53.800 --> 05:56.189
It's been two years.
When are you coming home?

05:56.720 --> 05:59.109
Not too quick.
I'm enjoying that apartment.

05:59.360 --> 06:01.954
-No, we miss you!
-Are you flying yet?

06:02.160 --> 06:06.915
-Or are the chimps doing the work?
- We got something to tell you.

06:08.720 --> 06:11.553
When you gonna make
that kind of commitment--

06:36.240 --> 06:39.357
MAN 1 : Captain Davidson,
report to the bridge.

06:48.960 --> 06:50.996
FRANK : Found it.
HANSEN: It's moving like a storm.

06:51.200 --> 06:53.873
It is. It's an electromagnetic storm.

06:54.080 --> 06:57.675
LEO: The digital clocks are stopped.
MARIA: It's beautiful.

06:57.880 --> 07:01.190
-So is the sun till you get close.
HANSEN: This is weird.

07:01.400 --> 07:05.075
HANSEN: I hear frequency patterns.
-Tune them in.

07:06.880 --> 07:10.555
HANSEN: It's electronic communication
from Earth, from all time.

07:10.800 --> 07:13.439
HANSEN:
The storm's bouncing it back to us.

07:14.640 --> 07:17.837
We'll start with a pass
through the core.

07:18.080 --> 07:22.073
T ake radiation gamma-ray reading.
Get your monkey ready.

07:22.280 --> 07:25.158
Sir, this is a waste of time.

07:25.360 --> 07:27.032
We have standard procedures--

07:27.280 --> 07:31.159
-l' m aware of the procedures, but--
-No manned flights.

07:31.400 --> 07:35.029
We send an ape. If it's safe,
we talk about a pilot.

07:35.240 --> 07:38.118
Why don't you just allow me
to do my job?

07:38.320 --> 07:42.632
He's the canary, that's the coal mine.
He launches at 1 6:00.

07:59.440 --> 08:03.752
Just follow your sequence
and come home. Understand? Home.

08:14.560 --> 08:18.269
VASICH: Stand by. Alpha pod launch
in 30 seconds.

08:34.320 --> 08:37.312
VASICH: Chart his course
to the eye of the storm.

08:39.039 --> 08:42.669
LEO:
Okay, Pericles, start sequence one.

08:49.840 --> 08:51.796
LEO:
Activate reading systems.

08:57.200 --> 08:58.679
LEO:
Ignition.

09:07.000 --> 09:10.072
VASICH: Have him start
taking perimeter readings.

09:15.560 --> 09:17.790
-What's wrong?
-He's off-course.

09:18.040 --> 09:19.075
Lock on him.

09:21.720 --> 09:23.278
He can't respond, sir.

09:23.480 --> 09:27.917
-There's a surge in the heart rate.
-Light him up again.

09:28.160 --> 09:29.878
I can't.

09:32.320 --> 09:33.355
He's gone.

09:33.920 --> 09:35.672
He's trained to come back.

09:36.520 --> 09:38.476
You think he's still alive?

09:42.000 --> 09:46.039
-Sir--
-For now, we just sit tight and wait.

09:47.360 --> 09:51.478
I'm gonna run some sequences
to see what he did wrong.

09:59.120 --> 10:02.430
HANSEN: The signal is breaking up.
VASlCH: He must be panicking.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.551
ALEXANDER:
He'll return to the Oberon.

10:04.800 --> 10:06.153
HANSEN:
I can 't hold him.

10:06.360 --> 10:07.998
VASICH:
That's it, we lost him.

10:08.240 --> 10:11.835
FRANK: Wanna send up another chimp?
-It's too dangerous.

10:12.040 --> 10:14.076
VASICH:
I won 't waste another pod.

10:14.320 --> 10:16.709
VASICH:
Shut down launch operations.

10:47.240 --> 10:48.593
Sir?

10:48.840 --> 10:50.592
Delta pod has launched.

10:53.280 --> 10:55.635
Your flight is not authorized!

10:55.840 --> 10:57.592
I' m going to get my chimp.

10:57.800 --> 11:01.156
VASICH: Bring that thing back here!
Return to base!

11:01.360 --> 11:04.272
Never send a monkey to do a man's job.

11:24.120 --> 11:26.111
I got a visual on Alpha pod.

11:41.400 --> 11:43.231
Oberon, come back!

11:56.120 --> 11:58.190
Oberon, come in!

12:08.480 --> 12:11.438
-l' m getting a mayday, sir.
-Alpha pod?

12:11.680 --> 12:14.956
-I don't know, but it's strong.
VASICH: Put it up.

12:16.040 --> 12:18.156
Mayday! Mayday! Come in!

12:18.400 --> 12:21.836
Request-- We 're going down! Mayday!

12:23.760 --> 12:25.193
Delta pod, abort.

15:03.000 --> 15:06.197
[APES YELL]

17:32.160 --> 17:33.957
This one looked at me.

17:40.320 --> 17:45.030
T ake your stinking hands off me,
you damn dirty human!

18:05.080 --> 18:07.310
GORILLA BOY 1 :
Stinking humans!

18:07.720 --> 18:09.711
GORILLA BOY 2:
You guys smell!

19:01.240 --> 19:03.151
Hey, where am l?

19:05.400 --> 19:06.913
What is this place?

19:17.880 --> 19:20.678
Here! I'm open! Come on!

19:20.960 --> 19:23.633
Dribble it down! Take it!

19:26.760 --> 19:29.399
GORILLA 3:
Make way! Clear the path!

19:29.640 --> 19:31.198
GORILLA BOY 4:
Get the humans!

19:34.680 --> 19:36.910
GORILLA BOY 2:
You guys smell!

19:38.360 --> 19:39.793
GORILLA BOY 4:
Take this!

19:43.400 --> 19:45.550
GORILLA BOY 1 : Stupid human!
ARI: Stop it!

19:48.800 --> 19:52.429
-Who said to throw stones at humans?
-My father.

19:52.640 --> 19:54.312
Well, he's wrong.

19:54.520 --> 19:57.592
-And you can tell him I said so.
-Human-lover.

20:18.400 --> 20:19.674
GORILLA 5:
Move along!

20:24.320 --> 20:27.676
Are you trying
to put me out of business?

20:28.000 --> 20:31.276
These are the skankiest, scabbiest...

20:31.520 --> 20:34.080
...scuzziest humans I've ever seen.

20:34.400 --> 20:38.234
-You don't want them?
-I'll take the whole lot.

20:39.840 --> 20:42.400
I must be out of my mind.

20:42.720 --> 20:44.995
I'll have to make it up on volume.

20:45.240 --> 20:47.913
All right, get them out...

20:48.120 --> 20:50.714
...and get them clean! Chop, chop!

20:56.520 --> 20:57.714
Let's go!

20:57.960 --> 20:59.552
Keep it moving!

20:59.800 --> 21:01.313
Come on! Hurry up!

21:05.600 --> 21:09.195
LIMBO: Gentlemen to the left!
Ladies to the right, please!

21:09.600 --> 21:10.794
Don't be afraid.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.594
Come on.

21:13.440 --> 21:17.194
Very touching. I can't see
for the tears in my eyes.

21:17.640 --> 21:20.473
Come on. That one's
crawling with lice.

21:22.440 --> 21:26.115
Check the teeth
on that little one. Nice.

21:35.880 --> 21:37.871
Stay back. Back!

21:39.720 --> 21:41.551
Get in there!

21:45.160 --> 21:46.878
Move! You too!

21:48.000 --> 21:53.074
How many times have I told you to
wear gloves when you handle humans?

21:57.760 --> 22:00.718
You normally hack off a limb, Limbo.

22:00.960 --> 22:03.713
Yes, general. That's true.

22:03.920 --> 22:07.071
LIMBO: Unfortunately,
they're worth more intact.

22:09.200 --> 22:11.760
Keep your eye on this one.

22:13.200 --> 22:15.077
He's feisty.

22:20.160 --> 22:23.550
Were these the ones
raiding the orchards?

22:23.800 --> 22:27.839
I know an old country remedy
that never fails.

22:28.160 --> 22:31.835
You gut one human,
and you string the carcass up.

22:32.040 --> 22:35.669
The Human Rights faction
is on me already.

22:35.920 --> 22:39.674
Do-gooders. Who needs them?
I' m for free speech as long as they...

22:41.760 --> 22:43.113
...keep their mouths shut.

22:43.280 --> 22:44.474
My niece wants one
for her birthday.

22:46.800 --> 22:51.078
Excellent. The little ones
make wonderful pets.

22:51.280 --> 22:54.477
But be sure
you get rid of it by puberty.

22:54.680 --> 22:59.231
One thing you don't want in your
house, it's a human teenager.

23:01.760 --> 23:04.957
Any one you'd like, sweetheart.

23:06.720 --> 23:08.472
That one.

23:09.080 --> 23:11.878
Oh, isn't she pretty.

23:16.640 --> 23:18.756
I'll get that for you, sir.

23:35.800 --> 23:39.509
And I have a pretty new collar...

23:40.040 --> 23:41.837
...just for you.

23:43.200 --> 23:44.997
Compliments of the house.

23:49.280 --> 23:51.510
You stink of humans.

24:02.880 --> 24:05.952
It's disgusting
the way we treat humans.

24:06.200 --> 24:08.668
It demeans us as much as them.

24:14.400 --> 24:16.152
Ari, let's go.

24:22.520 --> 24:26.479
Get them marked!
I got orders to fill!

24:46.400 --> 24:48.072
Next!

25:02.080 --> 25:03.399
Not you again.

25:03.600 --> 25:08.196
I can't stand by while humans
are being mistreated and tortured.

25:09.960 --> 25:14.351
The only reason I put up with your
nonsense is because of your father!

25:14.560 --> 25:17.518
You want me to stop?
Give up the business.

25:17.720 --> 25:20.951
Hey, I do the job
that nobody else wants!

25:21.280 --> 25:24.670
I don't see you bleeding-hearts
spending all day...

25:24.880 --> 25:28.395
...with these dangerous,
dirty, dumb beasts.

25:28.600 --> 25:32.070
They can be taught
to live with us as equals.

25:33.240 --> 25:34.798
I'm gonna prove it.

25:35.360 --> 25:37.351
LIMBO:
Don't do that.

25:37.760 --> 25:39.796
Don't do that.

25:41.440 --> 25:42.634
Stay back.

25:43.800 --> 25:45.995
Well, now there's your proof.

25:46.880 --> 25:49.110
Now I'm gonna have to put him down.

25:49.440 --> 25:50.714
Help me.

25:51.200 --> 25:52.394
Please.

25:53.600 --> 25:55.033
Please help me.

25:58.720 --> 26:00.790
You're giving me such a headache.

26:05.120 --> 26:07.190
I don't need this aggravation!

26:08.480 --> 26:09.595
Sell him to me.

26:09.920 --> 26:13.276
Are you crazy? He's wild.
They're both wild.

26:13.600 --> 26:14.953
Then I'll buy them both.

26:15.680 --> 26:18.399
That would be expensive.

26:19.680 --> 26:21.910
That would be...

26:22.240 --> 26:24.151
...very, very expensive.

26:30.720 --> 26:32.073
I'm sure we can...

26:32.480 --> 26:34.710
...you know, come to a deal.

26:36.640 --> 26:37.755
You know?

26:43.360 --> 26:45.430
Deliver them to my house.

26:48.960 --> 26:51.190
SANDAR:
Semos, help me!

26:52.960 --> 26:55.520
Rise when your master enters.

26:59.880 --> 27:01.836
Wild humans...

27:02.880 --> 27:04.950
...in my house.

27:05.520 --> 27:07.351
This one seems different.

27:07.560 --> 27:11.951
How could he be different?
You can't tell one from the other!

27:12.160 --> 27:13.752
My guests are here.

27:14.080 --> 27:17.675
Keep the savage ones out of sight.

27:22.280 --> 27:24.555
Especially from General Thade!

27:25.240 --> 27:27.629
SANDAR:
You'd better be nice to him!

27:31.080 --> 27:33.958
And wash your hands before dinner.

27:40.840 --> 27:44.549
Senator, good evening.
Dear, you look lovely tonight.

27:44.800 --> 27:47.189
But I'm having a bad hair day.

27:47.440 --> 27:50.159
Yet, she spends a fortune grooming.

27:50.480 --> 27:52.391
And I'm worth every penny.

27:54.160 --> 27:56.310
Would you like to freshen up?

27:57.680 --> 27:58.829
We're fine.

28:14.880 --> 28:19.271
-How'd these monkeys get like this?
-How else would they be?

28:19.520 --> 28:24.310
-They'd be begging me for a treat.
-What tribe are you from?

28:25.040 --> 28:27.759
U.S. Air Force. I'm going back to it.

28:42.800 --> 28:44.870
Finish your work.

28:49.520 --> 28:51.750
Please, everyone sit.

28:53.680 --> 28:56.877
We just returned
from our country house.

28:57.200 --> 28:59.111
-How was it?
-Boring.

28:59.440 --> 29:03.911
I find it relaxing being away
from the bustle of the city.

29:04.160 --> 29:06.310
NOVA:
There was no place to go.

29:06.640 --> 29:09.632
Nothing but trees and rocks.

29:09.840 --> 29:12.877
-All you did was nap.
-Exactly.

29:13.160 --> 29:15.515
Time away from politics...

29:15.720 --> 29:17.517
...is what I needed.

29:18.840 --> 29:23.311
We'd lose ourselves for days
in the forest when we were young.

29:23.520 --> 29:25.636
Now I can barely climb a tree.

29:26.240 --> 29:29.869
T rite but true:
"Youth is wasted on the young. "

29:31.160 --> 29:35.073
Oh, how did I get so old so fast?

29:35.280 --> 29:39.558
Living with your daughter
would age any ape quickly.

29:39.760 --> 29:42.194
SANDAR:
You've been a stranger lately.

29:42.400 --> 29:45.472
I apologize for my lateness, senator.

29:48.160 --> 29:50.196
I stopped to see my father.

29:50.400 --> 29:53.437
-How's my old friend?
-Slipping, I'm afraid.

29:53.640 --> 29:57.838
I'd like to see him more,
but these are troubled days.

29:58.080 --> 30:00.230
The humans infest the provinces.

30:00.440 --> 30:02.670
We encroach upon their habitat.

30:02.880 --> 30:06.111
They breed while we grow soft
in our affluence.

30:06.320 --> 30:08.675
THADE:
They outnumber us four to one!

30:08.880 --> 30:11.348
Why can't we simply
sterilize them all?

30:12.160 --> 30:14.230
The cost would be prohibitive.

30:14.560 --> 30:16.676
Although scientists tell me...

30:16.920 --> 30:20.117
...these humans
carry terrible diseases.

30:20.320 --> 30:21.673
How would we know?

30:21.880 --> 30:25.429
The army burns the bodies
before they' re examined.

30:29.200 --> 30:30.394
Father?

30:35.200 --> 30:39.637
At times, perhaps, the senate feels
that the army has been...

30:39.840 --> 30:41.432
...a tad extreme.

30:41.640 --> 30:46.839
Extremism in defense of apes
is no vice, senator!

30:47.160 --> 30:49.754
Your ideas threaten our prosperity!

30:50.400 --> 30:53.278
The human problem
can't be solved with money!

30:53.480 --> 30:56.517
We tried that once,
and all we got was...

30:56.720 --> 30:59.473
...a welfare state that nearly broke us.

30:59.720 --> 31:03.872
I think the city has about
as much diversity as I can handle.

31:04.480 --> 31:09.076
This garment was made
by one of my humans.

31:10.240 --> 31:12.708
And can you deny the skill?

31:13.360 --> 31:16.272
Obviously, they' re capable
of a real culture.

31:17.040 --> 31:21.636
Everything in the human culture
takes place below the waist.

31:28.480 --> 31:29.799
Bow your heads!

31:33.760 --> 31:36.718
We give thanks
for the fruit of the land.

31:36.920 --> 31:41.550
Bless us, holy father, who created
all apes in his image.

31:41.760 --> 31:46.959
Hasten the day when you will return
and bring peace to your children.

31:47.320 --> 31:49.754
-Amen.
GROUP: Amen.

31:56.960 --> 32:00.475
Next you'll be telling us
these beasts have a soul.

32:00.960 --> 32:02.234
Of course they do.

32:02.440 --> 32:06.194
The senator's daughter
flirts with blasphemy.

32:17.120 --> 32:19.839
Is there a soul in there?

32:32.400 --> 32:33.992
Do you have a towel?

32:41.120 --> 32:42.678
I've lost my appetite.

33:16.640 --> 33:19.029
I' m bored by these society dinners.

33:19.240 --> 33:22.949
-I came to see you.
-Oh, how sweet.

33:23.160 --> 33:25.037
You've wasted your time.

33:25.600 --> 33:27.591
My feelings haven't changed.

33:27.800 --> 33:30.268
I still care about you.

33:33.240 --> 33:37.870
You only care about my father's
influence. And your own ambition.

33:41.120 --> 33:44.271
I know about the trouble
you caused today.

33:44.480 --> 33:48.712
-I could have you arrested.
-I'd do it again.

33:49.760 --> 33:52.638
You feel so much for these humans...

33:53.280 --> 33:55.475
...yet you feel nothing for me.

34:08.000 --> 34:09.319
A moment, sir.

34:11.199 --> 34:12.518
What is it?

34:12.679 --> 34:16.355
We found something.
We think you should see it.

34:47.040 --> 34:48.268
There's a curfew.

34:48.480 --> 34:50.755
If they see you, they kill you.

34:51.120 --> 34:53.839
You stay here, you're already dead.

34:56.639 --> 34:59.234
Can you take me to
where we were caught?

34:59.920 --> 35:01.592
Not without my family.

35:20.200 --> 35:21.599
APE 1 :
This is where I saw it.

35:24.520 --> 35:25.509
THADE:
Go on.

35:26.920 --> 35:30.356
APE 2: Something fell from the sky
with wings of fire.

35:30.720 --> 35:34.679
APE 2: There was a thunderous sound
and the ground itself shook.

35:34.880 --> 35:38.668
-You weren't dreaming this?
-lt was no dream, sir.

35:38.880 --> 35:40.233
Look.

35:47.320 --> 35:49.880
-You told no one?
APE 1 : No, sir.

35:50.120 --> 35:52.634
APE 1 :
We had to come right to you.

35:54.320 --> 35:56.629
You did exactly the right thing.

36:43.320 --> 36:44.389
You smell that?

36:44.600 --> 36:47.068
Don't start now. We're off-duty.

36:47.280 --> 36:48.952
And I'm starving.

37:00.000 --> 37:01.228
You're hurt.

37:01.920 --> 37:03.638
How did you get away?

37:21.120 --> 37:23.759
-Who are you?
-Somebody trying to get out.

37:28.240 --> 37:30.470
She promised to take me back.

37:31.760 --> 37:35.719
This is a house-human.
He thinks he's better than us.

37:35.920 --> 37:36.830
Hey!

37:39.360 --> 37:40.918
We'll go together.

37:55.240 --> 37:56.798
[APES LAUGH]

37:58.240 --> 38:02.153
[APES CHATTER]

38:17.400 --> 38:19.994
[APES CHATTER]

38:29.720 --> 38:30.789
[NOVA SCREAMS]

39:08.480 --> 39:10.630
Good night, little girl.

39:22.200 --> 39:23.599
[SCREAMS]

39:33.760 --> 39:35.273
You go this way.

39:35.480 --> 39:37.436
The rest of you, come with me.

39:52.000 --> 39:54.355
ATTAR:
Send a squad to the north gate! Hurry!

39:55.920 --> 39:58.036
Wait! Someone's coming.

40:12.360 --> 40:14.794
You're lucky I found you first.

40:15.240 --> 40:17.754
Come on. I can reason with them.

40:17.960 --> 40:20.997
-We know how apes reason.
-How can we escape?

40:21.200 --> 40:23.714
Don't get involved with these humans.

40:24.520 --> 40:26.431
Why did you help me?

40:27.320 --> 40:29.436
Why would you take that chance?

40:30.800 --> 40:31.755
Because...

40:32.240 --> 40:35.550
...you're not usual.

40:36.120 --> 40:41.240
Show me a way out. I'll show you
something that will change your world.

40:45.440 --> 40:46.839
Trust me.

40:56.440 --> 40:57.714
When I was little...

40:57.960 --> 41:02.511
...I used to sneak outside the city,
where no one could find me.

41:04.760 --> 41:05.988
I can show you.

41:07.000 --> 41:09.639
If we're caught, no one can protect us!

41:10.320 --> 41:11.639
Trust me.

41:16.600 --> 41:18.238
What about her?

41:19.320 --> 41:23.836
-A human child won't survive.
-Bon can take her. Hide her at home.

41:39.240 --> 41:40.639
Check every house!

41:43.000 --> 41:46.197
APE 1 : Have you seen any humans?
-No.

41:55.320 --> 41:56.639
Hurry!

41:59.320 --> 42:01.754
-Father.
-I'll be right beside you.

42:01.960 --> 42:02.949
Come on!

42:19.440 --> 42:20.316
No!

42:23.320 --> 42:24.514
BIRN:
Stop!

42:29.720 --> 42:31.995
[GROANS]

42:49.800 --> 42:53.395
-Where are the other humans?
-Through the tunnels.

42:53.600 --> 42:56.034
When you find them, kill them all.

42:57.040 --> 43:01.397
Except for the troublemaker.
I want to talk to him before he dies.

43:02.040 --> 43:04.838
Sir, the senator's daughter is with them.

43:07.200 --> 43:11.637
-They took her?
-She's helping them. I saw her myself.

43:15.520 --> 43:18.830
She had no choice.
They threatened her life.

43:20.720 --> 43:25.840
I'll report to the Senate. They'll beat
their chests and ask for my help.

43:26.120 --> 43:28.429
They are weak without you, sir.

43:48.280 --> 43:51.078
-Your dad was brave.
-What do you know?

43:51.280 --> 43:52.269
[SHRlEKS]

43:55.000 --> 43:56.433
Let me go.

44:02.880 --> 44:06.236
Thade will come soon.
We can still go back.

44:08.320 --> 44:10.038
I can't now.

44:30.640 --> 44:32.437
That's where I flew in.

44:34.480 --> 44:35.515
You did that?

44:35.720 --> 44:37.278
No, my retroburners.

44:38.040 --> 44:42.033
-I'm sure he'll explain.
-He can't explain what can't exist.

44:42.280 --> 44:44.236
Talking monkeys can't exist.

44:50.440 --> 44:52.078
Apes.

44:52.280 --> 44:55.989
Monkeys are further down
the evolutionary ladder.

44:56.200 --> 44:59.033
Just above humans.

45:03.720 --> 45:05.233
Calm down, will you?

45:07.560 --> 45:09.357
[SHRlEKS]

45:10.480 --> 45:13.790
-What's wrong?
-Afraid of water. Apes can't swim.

45:14.000 --> 45:15.035
We drown.

45:15.280 --> 45:18.033
That's why every day we pray for rain.

45:43.360 --> 45:46.511
How long can a human
hold its breath underwater?

46:37.640 --> 46:41.235
Thought you were afraid of water.
Two dead monkey--

46:41.440 --> 46:43.192
Apes down at the bottom.

46:44.360 --> 46:46.794
Someone else knows you' re here.

47:07.520 --> 47:09.397
-What's that?
-A frequency with...

47:09.640 --> 47:11.676
... my ship so I can talk to them.

47:11.880 --> 47:12.835
It talks?

47:14.160 --> 47:15.354
With radio waves.

47:15.600 --> 47:17.033
Sorcery.

47:17.240 --> 47:18.992
Not sorcery, science.

47:28.200 --> 47:29.428
I have contact.

47:29.640 --> 47:33.235
They' re already here.
They must be waiting for me.

47:33.960 --> 47:35.996
LEO:
lt'll lead us to them.

47:37.680 --> 47:41.150
We' re in control now.
We' re the 800-pound gorilla.

47:44.560 --> 47:45.595
Who are you?

47:45.800 --> 47:48.439
Captain Leo Davidson.
Pilot, U.S. Air Force.

47:48.640 --> 47:51.632
-From planet Earth.
-Your apes let you fly?

47:51.840 --> 47:54.559
They live in zoos and do what we say.

47:56.600 --> 47:58.795
This is hostile.
I got 36 hours...

47:59.000 --> 48:02.390
...to find my friends
and I'm out of this nightmare.

48:02.680 --> 48:05.319
What happens to us?
Where do we go?

48:07.440 --> 48:09.954
You go nowhere. He belongs to me!

48:11.880 --> 48:12.676
Stop!

48:12.880 --> 48:14.677
You, I've had enough of!

48:27.880 --> 48:30.110
Take it easy, little fella.

48:30.320 --> 48:32.311
I'm not gonna hurt you.

48:32.800 --> 48:34.916
I wouldn't hurt my property.

48:37.760 --> 48:39.671
But I'll make an exception.

48:47.440 --> 48:50.318
No harm done. Come here, kid.

48:50.840 --> 48:52.558
Come here.

48:53.240 --> 48:57.153
You're not hurt, right? You're young.

48:57.400 --> 49:00.358
Oh, these kids.
They bounce right back.

49:01.400 --> 49:02.753
Play dead.

49:04.160 --> 49:06.196
-Kill him.
-Slave trader.

49:08.800 --> 49:12.076
You kill him, you lower
yourself to his level.

49:12.520 --> 49:13.714
Exactly.

49:15.240 --> 49:16.958
She is extremely smart.

49:17.200 --> 49:20.192
I've heard her talk
about apes and humans.

49:20.400 --> 49:24.313
"Separate but equal. "
"T o each his own. "

49:24.520 --> 49:26.750
Something like that. Right?

49:27.000 --> 49:29.833
LIMBO:
Whatever it is, I agree.

49:30.040 --> 49:32.634
Can't we all just get along?

49:37.640 --> 49:42.156
I'm probably just in the way.
So why don't I just get going?

49:44.280 --> 49:46.191
He'll lead them to us.

49:46.400 --> 49:48.356
Then we'll make him our guest.

49:49.200 --> 49:50.599
Cuff him.

49:56.440 --> 49:58.556
Ow! These things hurt.

50:03.240 --> 50:07.153
-What are you doing?
-You could use that against us.

50:07.400 --> 50:10.278
-Who invented that?
-lt was gonna save us.

50:10.480 --> 50:12.152
-We're better off now.
-We?

50:13.320 --> 50:15.880
-You're so difficult.
-Like a slave?

50:16.080 --> 50:18.355
-That's not what--
-Shut up!

50:19.360 --> 50:21.351
That goes for all species.

50:31.040 --> 50:35.955
If ever I thought those humans were
capable of kidnapping my daughter--

50:36.160 --> 50:38.515
Don't blame yourself, senator.

50:38.720 --> 50:41.598
You've been compassionate with them.

50:41.840 --> 50:43.796
Look how they've repaid you.

50:44.000 --> 50:45.797
Can you find her?

50:48.560 --> 50:50.232
If you untie my hands.

50:51.560 --> 50:53.357
What do you want?

50:53.600 --> 50:55.431
Declare martial law.

50:56.760 --> 50:58.796
Give me absolute power...

50:59.040 --> 51:02.350
...to rid this planet of humans
once and for all.

51:04.120 --> 51:08.159
Now is not the time to be timid
or indecisive.

51:08.920 --> 51:12.549
I' m the one who can bring
your daughter back alive.

51:31.000 --> 51:32.956
He's not in the city.

51:33.720 --> 51:35.597
We underestimate this human.

51:37.240 --> 51:38.753
I'll hunt him down.

51:47.640 --> 51:50.950
Your father sent me.
You must come quickly.

51:52.720 --> 51:55.757
Warn the outposts.
Don't let the humans pass.

51:56.000 --> 51:57.274
I understand, sir.

51:58.240 --> 52:01.073
Apart from my father,
I rely on you most.

52:01.280 --> 52:04.670
We are not just soldiers.
We are friends.

52:05.640 --> 52:06.914
I'll depend on you.

52:07.440 --> 52:08.589
Yes, sir.

52:23.840 --> 52:26.593
-So many questions I want to ask.
-Me too.

52:26.800 --> 52:28.392
ARI:
These "zoos"--

52:28.600 --> 52:31.717
What are they? This word is
not familiar.

52:31.920 --> 52:35.595
-Our last apes are in zoos.
-What happened to them?

52:35.800 --> 52:37.199
Gone.

52:37.400 --> 52:39.755
After we cut down the forests...

52:40.640 --> 52:42.551
...the ones who survived...

52:43.240 --> 52:45.356
...were locked up in cages.

52:45.600 --> 52:47.955
LEO:
Used for scientific experiment.

52:48.200 --> 52:51.795
-That's horrible.
-We do worse to our own kind.

52:52.000 --> 52:54.833
I don't understand.
You seem intelligent.

52:55.040 --> 52:58.794
Smarter we get, the more
dangerous our world becomes.

53:00.400 --> 53:02.595
I knew it. You're sensitive.

53:03.840 --> 53:05.751
Uncommon quality in a male.

53:07.600 --> 53:11.354
Why don't your apes object
to the way you treat them?

53:12.040 --> 53:13.314
They can't talk.

53:13.520 --> 53:17.149
Maybe they choose not to,
given the way you treat them.

53:19.160 --> 53:20.798
Apes in cages. Right.

53:43.800 --> 53:45.438
THADE:
Father.

53:49.240 --> 53:51.674
I don't have much time.

53:51.920 --> 53:54.832
T ell me about this human...

53:55.200 --> 53:56.997
...who troubles you.

53:57.720 --> 54:00.917
I will capture him
with little trouble.

54:02.640 --> 54:04.995
No. You're not telling me everything.

54:07.080 --> 54:09.799
You believe he is not born
of this world.

54:13.000 --> 54:14.956
Has he come alone?

54:15.440 --> 54:16.589
Yes.

54:17.640 --> 54:20.473
More will come looking for him.

54:20.680 --> 54:22.716
How can you possibly know?

54:26.320 --> 54:29.392
I have something to tell you.

54:30.120 --> 54:32.714
Something my father told me...

54:32.920 --> 54:36.435
...and his father told him.

54:36.680 --> 54:40.878
Back along our bloodlines to Semos.

54:42.480 --> 54:44.471
In the time before time...

54:44.720 --> 54:48.110
...we were the slaves
and the humans...

54:48.920 --> 54:50.353
...were the masters.

54:51.920 --> 54:53.239
Impossible.

55:16.400 --> 55:17.389
Break it.

55:35.920 --> 55:39.959
What you hold in your hand
is the proof of their power.

55:40.440 --> 55:42.271
Their power of invention.

55:42.520 --> 55:44.875
Their power of technology.

55:45.080 --> 55:50.029
Against this, our strength
means nothing.

55:53.280 --> 55:58.229
This has the power
of a thousand spears.

55:58.880 --> 56:00.233
I warn you.

56:00.440 --> 56:04.911
Their ingenuity goes hand in hand
with their cruelty.

56:06.440 --> 56:07.793
No creature...

56:08.000 --> 56:11.629
...is as devious, as violent.

56:11.840 --> 56:14.877
You must find this human quickly.

56:15.120 --> 56:19.238
Do not let him get to Calima.

56:19.720 --> 56:21.358
The forbidden area?

56:22.880 --> 56:27.795
Calima holds the secret
to our true beginnings.

56:31.040 --> 56:32.632
Damn them.

56:33.120 --> 56:35.588
I will stop him, Father.

56:36.920 --> 56:38.399
Damn them.

56:38.600 --> 56:41.637
Damn them all to hell.

57:21.320 --> 57:22.639
What is it?

57:23.120 --> 57:25.634
DAENA:
They' re to keep us away.

57:26.080 --> 57:28.435
LEO:
What's on the other side?

57:28.640 --> 57:31.473
It leads to the sacred
ruins at Calima.

57:31.880 --> 57:35.873
-What is that?
-Calima? That's where, well...

57:36.120 --> 57:39.874
...according to our holy writings,
creation began.

57:40.720 --> 57:45.077
Where the Almighty
breathed life into Semos...

57:45.280 --> 57:47.236
...the first ape.

57:47.720 --> 57:50.598
In the time before time.

57:53.400 --> 57:56.073
It is where Semos will return.

57:56.280 --> 58:01.229
Most educated apes consider
such religious notions as fairy tales.

58:02.280 --> 58:05.477
Metaphors we use to explain our origins.

58:05.680 --> 58:08.752
I doubt if there ever really was a Semos.

58:13.160 --> 58:15.833
LEO:
My crew is there, so we' re going.

58:16.280 --> 58:17.838
Doesn't he ever stop?

58:39.400 --> 58:42.073
-They' re scared of water?
-We'll cross somewhere else.

58:44.240 --> 58:47.471
No time. Gets dark,
we're going right through.

58:54.600 --> 58:56.477
Semos smiles on me.

58:56.680 --> 58:58.033
I win again.

59:00.120 --> 59:03.635
You win too often.
What's hidden up your sleeve?

59:05.520 --> 59:06.589
All of them.

59:08.680 --> 59:09.635
Cheater!

59:21.920 --> 59:24.832
-Who's in charge here?!
-I am, sir!

59:25.920 --> 59:29.196
-I didn't know--
-This camp is a disgrace.

59:29.920 --> 59:34.118
ATTAR: Some humans have escaped!
-lf they come, we will crush them.

59:34.320 --> 59:37.630
These humans are different.
They travel with apes.

59:38.360 --> 59:39.759
[LAUGHING]

59:42.040 --> 59:43.792
You find this amusing?

59:44.240 --> 59:45.593
No, sir.

59:45.800 --> 59:50.157
I'm assuming command.
This camp will be prepared!

01:00:11.720 --> 01:00:13.551
Just grab the reins.

01:00:13.760 --> 01:00:16.558
Hold tight. We're gonna
cross the river.

01:00:20.840 --> 01:00:24.628
Horses are great swimmers.
They'll carry you across.

01:00:30.440 --> 01:00:35.275
Good luck. Have a nice ride.
Leave me. I'll only slow you down.

01:00:35.480 --> 01:00:38.199
-Letting him go?
-No. He'll ride with us.

01:00:38.440 --> 01:00:42.035
No, wait. Wait. This is suicide.

01:00:42.280 --> 01:00:45.750
Only a human would think
that this could work.

01:00:46.720 --> 01:00:47.755
[GASPS]

01:01:04.040 --> 01:01:08.238
Hear my prayers, Semos,
father of all apes.

01:01:17.720 --> 01:01:19.551
[HORSE WHINNIES]

01:01:36.920 --> 01:01:38.956
No! No! I'm on your side!

01:01:45.960 --> 01:01:47.234
Come on!

01:02:02.200 --> 01:02:03.349
[ROARS]

01:02:16.280 --> 01:02:17.156
[GASPS]

01:02:57.040 --> 01:02:58.996
Come on! We have to swim.

01:02:59.800 --> 01:03:00.869
Hey!

01:03:01.640 --> 01:03:03.517
I won't let go of you!

01:03:03.760 --> 01:03:05.159
Come on!

01:03:32.520 --> 01:03:34.636
[GROWLS]

01:03:35.280 --> 01:03:37.510
[GROWLS]

01:03:45.440 --> 01:03:48.159
No, no, wait. There's no need now.

01:03:48.440 --> 01:03:49.953
-Says who?
-Them.

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:54.559
They tried to kill me like
I was nothing but a miserable--

01:03:56.680 --> 01:03:57.669
Human?

01:04:31.360 --> 01:04:32.395
Ow.

01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:33.959
You're hurt.

01:04:34.520 --> 01:04:36.750
She was holding on pretty tight.

01:04:38.360 --> 01:04:42.751
The soldiers will cross downstream.
We should move quickly!

01:04:50.280 --> 01:04:52.999
ATT AR: They crossed the river.
-You didn't stop them?

01:04:55.080 --> 01:04:56.957
ATT AR:
Horses carried them.

01:05:01.240 --> 01:05:02.559
Horses?

01:05:03.360 --> 01:05:05.510
Our horses, sir.

01:05:22.440 --> 01:05:23.589
[CHATTERS]

01:05:41.040 --> 01:05:44.749
Forgive me, my friend.
I' m not angry with you.

01:05:44.960 --> 01:05:46.598
Father was taken from me.

01:05:47.160 --> 01:05:51.392
He was a great leader
and a direct descendant of Semos.

01:05:51.720 --> 01:05:54.951
ATT AR:
Now it's time for you to lead.

01:05:56.800 --> 01:05:58.552
Form the divisions.

01:05:58.840 --> 01:05:59.909
Form divisions!

01:06:02.160 --> 01:06:03.070
[CHATTERS]

01:06:04.160 --> 01:06:05.559
Full battle ready!

01:06:08.760 --> 01:06:10.591
Sound the call to march!

01:06:40.400 --> 01:06:43.153
T omorrow we reach Calima.

01:06:56.920 --> 01:06:59.195
He'll stay like that all night.

01:07:00.960 --> 01:07:02.518
A soldier, isn't he?

01:07:02.720 --> 01:07:06.599
A general. Well, he was
until he opposed Thade.

01:07:06.840 --> 01:07:10.674
When Thade ruined his career,
my father took him in.

01:07:12.560 --> 01:07:15.996
He was a great soldier.
Attar was his best pupil.

01:07:16.640 --> 01:07:18.756
ARI:
Now they're enemies.

01:07:23.400 --> 01:07:25.675
I'd like to see your world.

01:07:26.160 --> 01:07:30.756
They'd probably prod you and poke you
and throw you in a cage.

01:07:33.400 --> 01:07:35.038
You'd protect me.

01:07:48.640 --> 01:07:50.949
They think you'll save them.

01:07:53.200 --> 01:07:57.113
After you meet your friends,
we'll never see you again.

01:07:58.840 --> 01:08:02.116
Well, I didn't promise them anything.

01:08:02.960 --> 01:08:04.154
No.

01:08:05.240 --> 01:08:07.879
You just dropped in from the stars.

01:09:19.040 --> 01:09:20.758
They're not here.

01:09:33.600 --> 01:09:34.749
LEO:
Hello?

01:09:48.359 --> 01:09:50.350
They were never here.

01:09:52.800 --> 01:09:54.756
You said they'd come for us.

01:10:21.440 --> 01:10:23.158
LEO:
That's impossible.

01:10:43.520 --> 01:10:44.350
What is it?

01:10:45.920 --> 01:10:47.558
It's my ship.

01:10:49.240 --> 01:10:52.357
These ruins are
thousands of years old.

01:10:53.240 --> 01:10:55.549
I was just here a few days ago.

01:11:12.440 --> 01:11:15.352
This is what I was
picking up. The Oberon.

01:11:24.040 --> 01:11:25.758
ARI:
What are you doing?

01:11:26.240 --> 01:11:29.357
It has a power source
that lasts forever.

01:11:40.640 --> 01:11:43.598
Maybe I can access
the ship's visual log.

01:11:44.440 --> 01:11:47.318
Then I can figure out what happened.

01:11:55.440 --> 01:11:57.590
Mayday! Come in, guidance!

01:11:57.840 --> 01:12:00.229
Request instructions!
Going down!

01:12:03.760 --> 01:12:07.833
We were searching for a pilot
in an electromagnetic storm.

01:12:08.840 --> 01:12:11.832
I got pushed forward through time.

01:12:12.840 --> 01:12:16.276
We haven 't had any communications
since we crashed.

01:12:17.120 --> 01:12:19.998
This planet is uncharted, uninhabited.

01:12:21.160 --> 01:12:25.392
The apes we 've brought along with us
are a lot stronger...

01:12:25.800 --> 01:12:27.028
...and a lot smarter...

01:12:27.440 --> 01:12:29.317
... than we ever imagined.

01:12:36.240 --> 01:12:37.958
Apes are out of control.

01:12:38.520 --> 01:12:39.999
One male named Semos...

01:12:41.040 --> 01:12:45.158
... who I raised myself,
has taken over the group.

01:12:45.360 --> 01:12:48.796
We have weapons but I don 't
think we 'll last long.

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:52.310
Maybe I saw the truth,
but I wouldn 't admit it.

01:12:52.520 --> 01:12:54.351
They were good students--

01:13:05.040 --> 01:13:07.759
They' re all dead
because they looked for me.

01:13:12.200 --> 01:13:14.555
We' re alive because of you.

01:13:37.440 --> 01:13:38.429
Who are they?

01:13:38.800 --> 01:13:41.553
Your story is spreading.
They want to see...

01:13:41.800 --> 01:13:44.360
...this human who defies the apes.

01:13:45.280 --> 01:13:46.793
Send them all back.

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:50.151
Where? They left their homes
to be with you.

01:15:00.600 --> 01:15:01.919
I saw them.

01:15:02.240 --> 01:15:03.434
How many?

01:15:03.640 --> 01:15:05.551
As far as I could see.

01:15:06.520 --> 01:15:10.354
Thade has all his legions.
The senate's capitulated.

01:15:11.160 --> 01:15:13.355
He answers to no one now.

01:15:18.560 --> 01:15:22.394
You' re gonna have to get your people
out of here.

01:15:23.120 --> 01:15:24.758
They won't listen to me.

01:15:38.320 --> 01:15:40.356
This is a fight we can't win.

01:15:41.440 --> 01:15:43.556
Break up and scatter.

01:15:44.200 --> 01:15:46.953
I'll draw them off.
I'm who they want.

01:15:48.720 --> 01:15:50.312
LEO:
All right? Come on!

01:15:50.840 --> 01:15:52.159
Let's go!

01:15:52.560 --> 01:15:53.959
Let's go!

01:15:57.040 --> 01:15:58.075
LEO:
Come on!

01:16:08.200 --> 01:16:10.634
You've gotta make them understand.

01:16:10.880 --> 01:16:13.155
It's over. No help is coming.

01:16:20.800 --> 01:16:22.153
You came.

01:16:49.240 --> 01:16:52.437
Stop!
Come closer and identify yourself!

01:16:57.440 --> 01:16:59.954
How dare you show your face here?!

01:17:00.960 --> 01:17:03.758
It is not my decision.

01:17:11.640 --> 01:17:13.756
I wish to speak to Thade.

01:17:39.280 --> 01:17:40.190
[SNARLS]

01:17:51.240 --> 01:17:52.639
Why have you come?

01:18:03.240 --> 01:18:04.958
T o be with you.

01:18:17.240 --> 01:18:18.309
A trade?

01:18:18.640 --> 01:18:22.189
You' re proposing that?
Yourself for the humans?

01:18:25.600 --> 01:18:29.195
Even when you were a child,
you took in stray humans.

01:18:29.400 --> 01:18:31.834
Your family indulged you.

01:18:36.160 --> 01:18:37.798
Look what you've become.

01:18:39.320 --> 01:18:40.753
I've been...

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:43.069
...mistaken.

01:18:46.040 --> 01:18:47.473
Forgive me.

01:19:04.560 --> 01:19:07.358
So you want to be human?

01:19:14.600 --> 01:19:16.352
Then wear their mark!

01:19:24.160 --> 01:19:25.229
Let her return.

01:19:26.120 --> 01:19:29.157
THADE:
She'll die with her friends tomorrow.

01:20:08.200 --> 01:20:13.149
We were searching for a pilot
in an electromagnetic storm.

01:20:13.560 --> 01:20:16.950
We haven 't had any communications
since we crashed.

01:20:17.160 --> 01:20:18.752
I' m so sorry.

01:20:21.240 --> 01:20:23.754
I' m responsible for all of this.

01:20:24.240 --> 01:20:26.356
And l' m never going home.

01:20:28.600 --> 01:20:30.272
Just like them.

01:20:33.240 --> 01:20:35.310
The apes are out of control.

01:20:47.040 --> 01:20:49.156
I can't go home, either.

01:20:50.840 --> 01:20:52.717
Maybe we' re not so different.

01:20:54.960 --> 01:20:58.430
No. We' re very different.

01:21:01.040 --> 01:21:03.952
You care about everybody but yourself.

01:21:05.040 --> 01:21:09.272
Doesn't matter. Apes, humans.
My planet, your planet.

01:21:09.480 --> 01:21:12.597
The universe rewards cruelty with power.

01:21:13.840 --> 01:21:14.955
No.

01:21:16.040 --> 01:21:19.828
Not always. Not if we fight back.

01:21:25.200 --> 01:21:27.156
I' m just not sure how.

01:21:34.560 --> 01:21:36.551
Better take care of that.

01:21:46.240 --> 01:21:49.152
KRULL:
I respect your courage.

01:21:50.040 --> 01:21:53.749
But my advice to you is
to put that away...

01:21:54.440 --> 01:21:56.590
...and head for the mountains.

01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:41.672
There's one possibility.

01:22:42.640 --> 01:22:45.473
I want those people behind the ship.

01:22:45.680 --> 01:22:48.956
-Not hiding, they need to be seen.
-And us?

01:22:49.360 --> 01:22:52.113
You'll be in front. You're the bait.

01:22:52.320 --> 01:22:54.993
-I won't move.
-You won't be there.

01:22:55.240 --> 01:22:59.552
-I can do this!
-I know. I need you back with them.

01:23:01.280 --> 01:23:02.633
We got one shot.

01:23:07.920 --> 01:23:09.194
LEO:
Listen!

01:23:09.600 --> 01:23:10.999
I got an idea.

01:23:11.240 --> 01:23:14.915
We may have a chance.
I need you behind the ship.

01:23:17.680 --> 01:23:19.796
Hey, we can win this.

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.151
It's been done before. On my planet.

01:23:23.920 --> 01:23:27.117
Men have done amazing things in history.

01:23:27.320 --> 01:23:29.197
That history belongs to you.

01:23:30.840 --> 01:23:34.355
Sometimes even a few
can make a difference, okay?

01:23:35.560 --> 01:23:40.395
This is the day you've waited for!
You get to stand up to the apes!

01:23:41.760 --> 01:23:42.954
Leo!

01:23:46.200 --> 01:23:49.033
You know you can't defeat Thade's army.

01:23:50.640 --> 01:23:54.349
We might confuse them.
It could give us a chance.

01:23:56.640 --> 01:24:01.395
You don't understand Thade.
He'll keep coming for you.

01:24:01.640 --> 01:24:03.039
No matter what.

01:24:03.520 --> 01:24:05.431
That's what I'm counting on.

01:24:46.400 --> 01:24:47.913
Get behind the ship!

01:24:48.200 --> 01:24:50.873
LEO:
Get children behind the ship!

01:24:52.520 --> 01:24:54.078
Come on, move! Now!

01:25:13.840 --> 01:25:15.159
-Let me go.
-No.

01:25:15.360 --> 01:25:18.193
-Let me prove I can help!
-I need you here.

01:25:18.440 --> 01:25:20.158
Help clear them back.

01:25:43.640 --> 01:25:45.198
-What?
-I'm part of this!

01:25:45.400 --> 01:25:46.958
-Get back!
-No!

01:25:47.200 --> 01:25:48.553
BIRN:
I'm staying!

01:25:58.240 --> 01:26:00.356
Send in the first wave.

01:26:00.560 --> 01:26:03.313
[ROARS]

01:26:06.480 --> 01:26:07.469
Here they come.

01:26:09.560 --> 01:26:10.788
Now!

01:26:23.480 --> 01:26:25.152
Oh, God.

01:26:52.000 --> 01:26:52.989
Come on.

01:27:11.720 --> 01:27:12.709
Jesus!

01:27:20.600 --> 01:27:21.953
Come on.

01:28:13.800 --> 01:28:14.915
Wait.

01:28:34.600 --> 01:28:36.272
Now! Go!

01:28:50.440 --> 01:28:53.557
With that weapon,
we cannot defeat them!

01:29:07.400 --> 01:29:09.550
I'm tired of this human.

01:30:21.920 --> 01:30:23.353
No! Wait!

01:31:22.640 --> 01:31:25.950
My fight is with Thade, not you!

01:31:26.200 --> 01:31:28.760
Then your fight is with me!

01:32:40.720 --> 01:32:44.315
[ENGINE ROARS]

01:34:12.800 --> 01:34:14.392
Semos.

01:34:46.920 --> 01:34:49.593
Pericles. A better landing than me.

01:34:53.800 --> 01:34:56.394
Sir, the prophecy is true.

01:34:56.600 --> 01:34:59.034
Semos has returned to us.

01:35:02.200 --> 01:35:03.315
Come on.

01:35:04.240 --> 01:35:07.198
Let's go explain evolution
to the monkeys.

01:35:20.840 --> 01:35:23.308
[PERICLES CHATTERS]

01:38:18.680 --> 01:38:20.671
He'll turn us into slaves!

01:38:20.960 --> 01:38:21.949
Kill him!

01:38:22.240 --> 01:38:25.118
Listen. This is where you're from.

01:38:25.320 --> 01:38:30.394
We brought you here. It's true.
We lived in peace together. Semos...

01:38:30.640 --> 01:38:32.392
...killed everybody.

01:38:38.000 --> 01:38:39.115
He's lying!

01:38:39.680 --> 01:38:40.749
Help me!

01:38:41.200 --> 01:38:44.431
My friend, kill him!

01:38:52.080 --> 01:38:54.594
Everything I have believed is a lie!

01:38:55.000 --> 01:38:58.754
ATT AR:
You and your family have betrayed us!

01:38:59.280 --> 01:39:01.953
I won't help you anymore.

01:39:10.240 --> 01:39:11.798
Ari....

01:39:17.160 --> 01:39:19.196
[GRUNTS]

01:40:58.360 --> 01:40:59.349
You okay?

01:41:00.080 --> 01:41:01.798
You came home.

01:41:02.080 --> 01:41:05.390
It's safe.
You can come out now.

01:41:08.040 --> 01:41:09.598
What? It's over?

01:41:09.880 --> 01:41:12.952
I was just getting ready
to make my move.

01:41:23.240 --> 01:41:26.038
ATT AR:
We'll leave the graves unmarked.

01:41:26.240 --> 01:41:30.199
No one who comes will be able
to tell apes from humans.

01:41:30.400 --> 01:41:32.118
They'll be mourned together...

01:41:32.760 --> 01:41:36.196
...as it should be, from now on.

01:41:48.240 --> 01:41:50.196
T ake good care of him, okay?

01:41:50.960 --> 01:41:54.475
I can promise you
I won't put him in a cage.

01:41:57.040 --> 01:41:59.395
[BEEPS]

01:42:10.800 --> 01:42:13.598
It found the storm
that brought me here.

01:42:14.400 --> 01:42:15.753
You know...

01:42:16.280 --> 01:42:19.033
...it would mean much to everyone...

01:42:19.280 --> 01:42:20.998
...if you would stay.

01:42:24.400 --> 01:42:26.118
Would mean much to me.

01:42:27.240 --> 01:42:29.037
I have to leave now.

01:42:29.280 --> 01:42:31.236
I have to get back.

01:42:36.280 --> 01:42:39.431
You know, one day,
they'll tell a story...

01:42:39.640 --> 01:42:43.599
...about a human who came
from the stars...

01:42:44.240 --> 01:42:45.992
...and changed our world.

01:42:48.800 --> 01:42:51.598
Some will say it was just
a fairy tale...

01:42:54.600 --> 01:42:56.795
...that he was never real.

01:42:59.200 --> 01:43:00.952
But I'll know.

01:43:21.680 --> 01:43:22.476
Oh.

01:43:22.800 --> 01:43:23.789
Keep it.

01:43:24.680 --> 01:43:27.399
You know, I'd like to thank you...

01:43:27.600 --> 01:43:32.799
...for opening my eyes to a brave new
world of trade with the humans.

01:43:34.040 --> 01:43:35.393
Yeah, no problem.

01:43:35.760 --> 01:43:37.830
Farewell, spaceman.

01:43:38.360 --> 01:43:42.797
All right, kids, who wants
to buy some aspirin?

01:43:54.240 --> 01:43:55.878
Maybe you'll come back.

01:46:06.560 --> 01:46:11.475
